node.text:
To defeat an enemy against humanity, it takes all of us. June 6, 1944, also known as D-Day, was a crucial moment in the second World War. It took strategy, strength, and most of all, selflessness to achieve victory, but none of it could have come without sacrifice. We remember D-Day and the men who gave it their all for a better world tomorrow.

Happy #PresidentsDay from the ones keeping the President on the move! Here are some fun facts about the world’s fanciest, most functional ride: Air Force One. 
 
✈️ Air Force One is not just one plane—it’s a term used for any @usairforce aircraft carrying the President. 
✈️ Because the President may need to travel to the furthest locations at any given time, Air Force One is capable of refueling midair giving it unlimited range.
✈️ Air Force One is a technological marvel! These aircraft are equipped with advanced secure communications equipment, allowing the aircraft to function as a mobile command center in the event of an emergency.
✈️ Can you say spacious? Air Force One has over 4,000 square feet of floor space on three levels, including an extensive suite for the President, a conference room, a medical suite that can function as an operating room, and two food preparation galleys that can feed 100 people at a time.

How’s this for #MondayMotivation?

The @usairforce Warrior Medics have stepped up to the plate once again in the fight against COVID-19. The Wilford Hall pathology lab is conducting its own testing on samples taken from patients suspected of having the illness. The lab’s main priority is supporting the 37th TRW and Basic Military Training with in-house testing that allows for quicker results, keeping the Air Force pipeline flowing as smoothly as possible in this trying time.
#AimHigh #FlyFightWin #USAF #USAFRecruiting #AirForce #AirForceRecruiting

Imagine yelling in a room this big and NOT hearing an echo. That’s what you’d experience in this anechoic chamber!

Oh no, I hope I don’t fall 🪂 

Aircrew Egress Systems specialists know the power of a good backup plan. Masters of the “Plan B,” these experts are in charge of keeping the aircraft seats, hatches, canopies, and parachutes functioning properly. So, if an aircraft *does* go down, the pilots don’t have to go down with it.

They say friendship runs deep, but in the @usairforce it also flies high. 

Capt Louis Bloom, 36th Fighter Squadron F-16 pilot, left, and Maj Chris Ng, 51st Medical Operations Squadron general surgeon, are truly forever friends. In fact, Maj Ng was key to helping Capt Bloom recover after he got into a motorcycle accident. He used his medical expertise to aid his fellow Airman (and friend) in a full and speedy recovery. 

Despite their initial flight delay, they’re in the cockpit together now. #InternationalDayofFriendship #FriendshipDay
